FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1775139065
OL,3,C'Hazardous gases' released at school
OL,4,Cas staff advised to attend hospital
OL,6,FTwo fire appliances from Coleraine
OL,7,FFire Station alongside one from both
OL,8,FPortstewart and Portrush stations
OL,9,Fattended.
OL,11,FIn a statement, the school's
OL,12,Fheadmaster, Dr David Carruthers said:
OL,13,F"There has been a chemical incident at
OL,14,FColeraine Grammar School which
OL,15,Fresulted in hazardous gases being
OL,16,Freleased in a confined area.
OL,18,F"No pupils were on site due to the
OL,19,FEaster holiday and three members of
OL,20,Fstaff were advised to attend hospital.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/4
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
